940
01:06:49,046 --> 01:06:50,486
...daughter...

941
01:06:52,246 --> 01:06:55,606
...of a blind Lithuanian
violin maker."

942
01:06:57,046 --> 01:07:00,806
It's fear. It was all about fear.
Fear's what kept them together.

943
01:07:01,046 --> 01:07:04,406
This whole time I've idealized
my grandparents' marriage.

944
01:07:04,646 --> 01:07:07,126
But this was not the love of the ages.

945
01:07:07,446 --> 01:07:10,566
The two stayed together
because they were terrified.

946
01:07:10,726 --> 01:07:13,926
Fear of loneliness, fear of failure,
fear of the unknown.

947
01:07:14,166 --> 01:07:17,766
Sure, fear. That's the main
motivator for everything.

948
01:07:18,006 --> 01:07:21,445
That and guilt are the two emotions
that keep a society humming.

949
01:07:21,685 --> 01:07:24,005
You and Rachel stay together
because of fear?

950
01:07:24,245 --> 01:07:26,005
-In a word, yes.
-You're okay with that?

951
01:07:26,325 --> 01:07:28,485
In three words, yes and no.

952
01:07:29,045 --> 01:07:32,885
See, it's not that simple.
You're looking for clear-cut answers.

953
01:07:33,125 --> 01:07:36,565
In reality, there's nothing clear-cut.
Life is not clear-cut.

954
01:07:36,805 --> 01:07:38,805
Life is gray.

955
01:07:39,045 --> 01:07:40,325
For instance:

956
01:07:42,165 --> 01:07:44,005
What do you see right here?

957
01:07:46,005 --> 01:07:49,284
-What are you asking me?
-I'm asking you, what do you see?

958
01:07:49,524 --> 01:07:51,044
I see your ass.

959
01:07:51,444 --> 01:07:55,684
That's what you think you see.
But in reality, there is no ass.

960
01:07:57,284 --> 01:08:00,164
