There is no ass."

981
01:09:12,802 --> 01:09:15,602
What a disappointment
you've turned out to be.

982
01:09:18,561 --> 01:09:20,321
Just promise me one thing.

983
01:09:20,561 --> 01:09:24,401
Please promise me that you will not
say any of this to Rachel.

984
01:09:24,641 --> 01:09:27,361
Are you crazy?
This conversation ends here.

985
01:09:27,921 --> 01:09:30,561
When Stan called me,
I couldn't believe it.

986
01:09:30,801 --> 01:09:32,801
I knew it was rough for you guys--

987
01:09:33,041 --> 01:09:36,081
We didn't wanna say until we knew
we weren't getting back together.

988
01:09:36,321 --> 01:09:37,841
Oh, my God.

989
01:09:40,561 --> 01:09:41,681
How are you doing?

990
01:09:41,921 --> 01:09:44,801
I don't know.
I thought I'd be devastated.

991
01:09:45,041 --> 01:09:47,440
Maybe it just hasn't hit me.

992
01:09:49,840 --> 01:09:53,280
-You're having an affair.
-What are you talking about?

993
01:09:53,520 --> 01:09:56,320
You're only not devastated
if you're seeing someone else.

994
01:09:56,480 --> 01:09:58,160
I'm not seeing someone else.

995
01:09:58,320 --> 01:10:00,320
Are you serious about
who you're not seeing?

996
01:10:00,560 --> 01:10:02,960
I don't know.
I know he's nothing like Ben.

997
01:10:03,120 --> 01:10:06,160
He's responsible, plans ahead,
has a Swiss Army knife.

998
01:10:06,400 --> 01:10:08,000
He even wants to cook me dinner.

999
01:10:08,160 --> 01:10:09,760
-He's a sandbag.
-A what?

1000
01:10:10,000 --> 01:10:12,480
He's just a sandbag
against the storm...

1001
01:10:12,720 --> 01:10:15,680
...holding off the inevitable
devastation.

1002
01:10:18,479 --> 01:10:20,239
Rachel, you okay?

1003
01:10:22,959 --> 01:10:24,159
Honey?

1004
01:10:26,719 --> 01:10:28,079
I'm sorry.

1005
01:10:29,519 --> 01:10:32,959
I know I'm supposed to be the one
holding your hand...

1006
01:10:33,199 --> 01:10:35,119
...but I just feel terrible.

1007
01:10:35,839 --> 01:10:39,199
I mean, the thought of you guys
not being together....

1008
01:10:39,359 --> 01:10:40,719
You're our best friends.

1009
01:10:41,519 --> 01:10:45,359
Fourth of Julys and Thanksgivings
and Christmases.

1010
01:10:45,999 --> 01:10:48,638
You guys were our
Fred and Ethel Mertz.

1011
01:10:49,118 --> 01:10:51,998
We thought you guys were
our Fred and Ethel Mertz.

1012
01:10:53,118 --> 01:10:54,478
Really?

1013
01:10:54,798 --> 01:10:58,878
I never thought this was
going to happen to me and Ben.

1014
01:10:59,118 --> 01:11:02,718
I thought we were going to be the ones
to go the distance.

1015
01:11:02,958 --> 01:11:07,758
But I just couldn't seem to get him
to put down that purple crayon.

1016
01:11:08,718 --> 01:11:12,718
But that's Ben.
That's who you fell in love with.

1017
01:11:12,958 --> 01:11:15,838
Katie, you are at 80
who you are at 8.

1018
01:11:16,078 --> 01:11:18,637
People don't change!

1019
01:11:19,037 --> 01:11:22,237
People change over time.
You've got to expect that.

1020
01:11:22,397 --> 01:11:27,357
The only way a relationship works is
if people grow and change together.

1021
01:11:28,637 --> 01:11:30,557
Mr. and Mrs. Cogen, Mr. Jordan.

1022
01:11:30,877 --> 01:11:35,117
Nice to have you tonight. Is Mrs.
Jordan not joining us this evening?

1023
01:11:35,357 --> 01:11:39,197
No, she's not. Stan, I told you
to make the reservation for three!

1024
01:11:39,437 --> 01:11:41,757
-I forgot.
-How could you forget that?

1025
01:11:41,917 --> 01:11:44,557
Say it louder. The guy
in the lot didn't hear you.

1026
01:11:44,797 --> 01:11:46,396
It wasn't that loud.

1027
01:11:53,116 --> 01:11:55,196
Did you see Sunday's 7 down?

1028
01:11:55,436 --> 01:11:57,676
-I missed that one.
-Five-letter word.

1029
01:11:57,996 --> 01:12:00,316
"Wants, requirements."

1030
01:12:00,716 --> 01:12:02,556
Rhymes with weeds.

1031
01:12:02,796 --> 01:12:03,836
"Needs"?

1032
01:12:04,076 --> 01:12:06,796
Exactly.
It was a direct attack on me.

1033
01:12:07,036 --> 01:12:08,956
Come on. You're being silly.

1034
01:12:09,116 --> 01:12:11,436
It was just a clue
in a crossword puzzle.

1035
01:12:11,996 --> 01:12:15,915
I know my wife.
She was specifically attacking me.

1036
01:12:16,235 --> 01:12:17,435
And for what?

1037
01:12:17,755 --> 01:12:19,435
For having needs.

1038
01:12:20,235 --> 01:12:22,395
Like having needs is
some terrible thing.

1039
01:12:22,875 --> 01:12:25,915
Show me one person
that doesn't have needs.

1040
01:12:28,475 --> 01:12:31,595
Try this bread dipped in
the olive oil. It's delicious.

1041
01:12:31,835 --> 01:12:33,275
Stan, give Ben the bread!

1042
01:12:33,595 --> 01:12:34,795
Why must you yell?

1043
01:12:34,955 --> 01:12:36,235
-Who yelled?
-You.

1044
01:12:36,475 --> 01:12:37,275
That's not a yell.

1045
01:12:37,595 --> 01:12:39,915
He hears everything as a yell.

1046
01:12:40,155 --> 01:12:42,475
On anyone's yell-o-meter,
that was a yell.

1047
01:12:42,715 --> 01:12:44,875
Was that a yell?
He didn't hear it as a yell.

1048
01:12:45,115 --> 01:12:47,274
His mom was a yeller.
He still hears her.

1049
01:12:47,514 --> 01:12:49,994
How could I hear her?
You drown her out.

1050
01:12:50,234 --> 01:12:51,274
It's true.

1051
01:12:51,514 --> 01:12:53,834
The last few years,
when Katie opened her mouth...

1052
01:12:54,154 --> 01:12:55,914
...all I'd hear was her mother.

1053
01:12:56,874 --> 01:12:57,914
Dot.

1054
01:12:58,714 --> 01:13:03,194
It wasn't easy for Katie to be raised
by a woman as complicated as Dot.

1055
01:13:03,514 --> 01:13:05,434
Please, she wasn't complicated.

1056
01:13:05,674 --> 01:13:09,434
She was an idiot who made
everyone else's life complicated.

1057
01:13:09,674 --> 01:13:13,114
You wouldn't believe the beautiful
psychological heirlooms...

1058
01:13:13,354 --> 01:13:15,513
...this snapping turtle handed down.

1059
01:13:15,833 --> 01:13:18,313
Everything's gotta be
in a neat little box...

1060
01:13:18,553 --> 01:13:20,873
...with a little blue bow on it.

1061
01:13:21,193 --> 01:13:22,553
Punctual.

1062
01:13:22,793 --> 01:13:23,993
Ordered.

1063
01:13:24,233 --> 01:13:27,353
God forbid anything unexpected
should happen...

1064
01:13:27,593 --> 01:13:30,953
...any perchances, happenstances...

1065
01:13:31,193 --> 01:13:33,993
...left turns, serendipities!

1066
01:13:34,233 --> 01:13:36,793
Nope, no way! Not allowed!

1067
01:13:37,033 --> 01:13:39,433
Out-of-bounds! Foul ball!

1068
01:13:39,673 --> 01:13:43,753
15-yard penalty!
Too much time being spontaneous!

1069
01:13:43,993 --> 01:13:47,112
Everything's gotta be connected.
Gotta connect the dots.

1070
01:13:47,352 --> 01:13:49,432
Maybe that's why they call her Dot.

1071
01:13:49,672 --> 01:13:53,192
You notice that her name wasn't
Gay or Joy or Fun!

1072
01:13:53,512 --> 01:13:54,792
Try the bread--

1073
01:13:54,952 --> 01:13:57,592
You can't even fuck
unless everything's just right!

1074
01:13:58,232 --> 01:14:02,472
Like a plane waiting for takeoff.
Windows shut? Check.

1075
01:14:02,712 --> 01:14:06,312
Doors locked? Check!
Heat on? Check!

1076
01:14:06,552 --> 01:14:09,352
Have we covered every possible,
single reason...

1077
01:14:09,592 --> 01:14:11,192
...why everything is my fault?!

1078
01:14:11,512 --> 01:14:16,071
Houston, we got a problem
and her name is Dot!

1079
01:14:16,231 --> 01:14:19,191
-Ben, bread.
-There are people like Katie and Dot...

1080
01:14:19,351 --> 01:14:22,071
...who color inside the lines,
and people like you...

1081
01:14:22,311 --> 01:14:25,511
...who wander outside.
That can be a very endearing quality.

1082
01:14:25,751 --> 01:14:29,111
That's why Katie fell in love
with you. Once you have kids--

1083
01:14:29,351 --> 01:14:31,031
I am not a third child!

1084
01:14:31,351 --> 01:14:33,991
Excuse me if my watch
has no hands on it.

1085
01:14:34,231 --> 01:14:37,991
That's fine. It's just, somebody
has to establish the routine--

1086
01:14:38,231 --> 01:14:40,551
Are you saying it's all my fault?!

1087
01:14:41,511 --> 01:14:43,031
It's nobody's fault!

1088
01:14:43,191 --> 01:14:46,390
When people say it's nobody's fault,
they don't mean that.

1089
01:14:46,630 --> 01:14:50,070
They mean it's your fault!
The nobody's fault things are...

1090
01:14:50,390 --> 01:14:53,910
...hurricanes, earthquakes,
tornadoes, acts of God!

1091
01:14:54,150 --> 01:14:58,070
But when a marriage fails,
it's gotta be somebody's fault!

1092
01:14:58,310 --> 01:14:59,510
And it's not mine!

1093
01:15:00,710 --> 01:15:04,230
Take that fucking bread and shove it
up the tops of your legs!

1094
01:15:47,348 --> 01:15:51,588
Maybe I'm tired! Maybe I'm dealing
with 5000 things all day long!

1095
01:15:51,828 --> 01:15:54,388
Maybe every need you have
doesn't have to be met...

1096
01:15:54,628 --> 01:15:56,948
...at the exact moment
you need it to be met!

1097
01:15:57,108 --> 01:16:00,868
I'm sick and tired of being
the designated driver of this marriage!

1098
01:16:01,108 --> 01:16:03,988
Nobody designated you!
It's a role you gave yourself!

1099
01:16:04,308 --> 01:16:07,188
Not once have you seen it
through my eyes!

1100
01:16:07,508 --> 01:16:10,868
We don't have a pea under our mattress.
You know what we have?

1101
01:16:11,108 --> 01:16:13,508
A fucking watermelon!

1102
01:16:23,507 --> 01:16:24,947
You okay?

1103
01:16:26,787 --> 01:16:28,627
Take me to Katie's.

1104
01:16:33,507 --> 01:16:35,187
What are you doing here?

1105
01:16:35,827 --> 01:16:38,307
I wanted to know what
your high was today.

1106
01:16:40,067 --> 01:16:42,147
You should've called.

1107
01:16:42,787 --> 01:16:44,546
My high was about you.

1108
01:16:47,666 --> 01:16:50,626
Tonight I saw myself
through your eyes.

1109
01:16:55,586 --> 01:16:56,786
And I'm sorry.

1110
01:16:57,186 --> 01:16:58,786
It might be a nice touch...

1111
01:16:59,026 --> 01:17:02,226
...if you add some roasted peanuts
to the sesame--

1112
01:17:08,466 --> 01:17:11,586
At some point we should discuss
how to tell the children.

1113
01:17:43,584 --> 01:17:45,664
How you doing? Come on in.

1114
01:17:46,784 --> 01:17:48,144
This is nice.

1115
01:17:48,384 --> 01:17:49,344
Thanks.

1116
01:17:49,584 --> 01:17:52,544
It's close to the park.
The kids and I can walk.

1117
01:17:52,864 --> 01:17:54,944
You want something to drink?

1118
01:17:55,104 --> 01:17:57,984
I'll take water if you don't have
anything else.

1119
01:18:00,624 --> 01:18:02,624
We have pretty much
anything you want.

1120
01:18:02,944 --> 01:18:04,784
Beer, Gatorade...

1121
01:18:04,944 --> 01:18:07,184
...fruit juice, iced tea.

1122
01:18:07,424 --> 01:18:09,024
Iced tea is fine.

1123
01:18:16,623 --> 01:18:17,503
Here you go.

1124
01:18:18,143 --> 01:18:19,583
You have a watch.

1125
01:18:22,063 --> 01:18:23,423
Come on in.

1126
01:18:25,503 --> 01:18:26,783
Sit down here.

1127
01:18:37,023 --> 01:18:39,023
I think we should....

1128
01:18:40,943 --> 01:18:45,182
When we pick the kids up Thursday,
we should just tell them that night.

1129
01:18:46,302 --> 01:18:49,262
We don't have to tell them right away.

1130
01:18:49,502 --> 01:18:50,702
Why?

1131
01:18:51,022 --> 01:18:53,502
What will change
between now and Thursday?

1132
01:18:55,662 --> 01:18:57,822
Katie, you're seeing someone else.

1133
01:18:58,142 --> 01:19:00,302
I'm not seeing him.

1134
01:19:00,622 --> 01:19:02,462
We're just talking.

1135
01:19:04,382 --> 01:19:05,422
Right.

1136
01:19:09,022 --> 01:19:12,541
I won't put up with any more of this
bullshit lying to the kids.

1137
01:19:12,781 --> 01:19:16,461
We take them to Chow Fun's, their
favorite restaurant, to tell them.

1138
01:19:16,701 --> 01:19:19,421
We can't really talk at Chow Fun's.

1139
01:19:19,661 --> 01:19:22,061
We'll go to the house
and tell them at dinner.

1140
01:19:22,381 --> 01:19:23,261
After dinner.

1141
01:19:23,581 --> 01:19:26,141
We'll all sit down and....

1142
01:19:26,381 --> 01:19:28,861
Jesus, how do we say this?

1143
01:19:32,301 --> 01:19:36,221
We'll just tell them
how much we love them...

1144
01:19:37,181 --> 01:19:39,341
...how amazing and beautiful
they are...

1145
01:19:39,581 --> 01:19:42,700
...so they don't think
that any of this is their fault.

1146
01:19:42,940 --> 01:19:44,860
That's the important thing.

1147
01:19:46,540 --> 01:19:48,220
We'll just say that...

1148
01:19:48,780 --> 01:19:50,540
...Mommy and Daddy...

1149
01:19:52,220 --> 01:19:54,300
...or Mom and Dad....

1150
01:19:55,100 --> 01:19:56,380
You think Mom and Dad?

1151
01:19:56,700 --> 01:19:57,900
Mommy and Daddy.

1152
01:19:59,980 --> 01:20:02,700
We'll say that Mommy and Daddy
have grown apart.

1153
01:20:03,340 --> 01:20:07,100
I was just thinking about Erin.
She'll probably say something like:

1154
01:20:07,340 --> 01:20:11,020
"Well, there must be something right
about you guys...

1155
01:20:11,260 --> 01:20:15,339
...for you to produce
such beautiful and amazing kids."

1156
01:20:19,019 --> 01:20:21,739
She might say something like that,
you know?

1157
01:20:30,699 --> 01:20:33,019
We'll just tell her that they were...

1158
01:20:34,459 --> 01:20:36,619
...born in love and we'll
always love them...

1159
01:20:36,859 --> 01:20:39,579
...but Mommy and Daddy
don't love each other anymore.

1160
01:20:41,498 --> 01:20:45,418
Well, wouldn't it be better
if we told them...

1161
01:20:48,378 --> 01:20:51,738
...we still love each other,
but in a different way?

1162
01:20:53,658 --> 01:20:54,778
Fine.

1163
01:20:56,058 --> 01:20:58,778
-We shouldn't say that?
-I said it was fine.

1164
01:20:59,658 --> 01:21:02,618
Well, it was kind of a weird "fine."

1165
01:21:03,818 --> 01:21:08,298
Should I be thrilled about how we
love each other in a different way?

1166
01:21:19,657 --> 01:21:22,377
-Who is it?
-Mr. Jordan, your couch is here.

1167
01:21:22,537 --> 01:21:25,577
Where have you guys been?
Come on in.

1168
01:21:27,097 --> 01:21:29,977
They were supposed to be here
first thing this morning.

1169
01:21:36,297 --> 01:21:39,017
I'll pick you up at 5:00
on Thursday?

1170
01:21:53,176 --> 01:21:54,536
So is there...

1171
01:21:55,816 --> 01:21:57,736
...anything else
we need to talk about?

1172
01:21:58,136 --> 01:21:59,176
Like what?

1173
01:22:02,536 --> 01:22:03,576
Nothing.

1174
01:22:06,856 --> 01:22:07,896
Bye.

1175
01:22:29,575 --> 01:22:30,855
What happened to you?

1176
01:22:31,175 --> 01:22:34,215
What happened to that fun girl
with the pith helmet?

1177
01:22:34,375 --> 01:22:38,455
You don't think I ask myself
that every day?

1178
01:22:38,775 --> 01:22:40,534
I'm talking about a connection!

1179
01:22:40,694 --> 01:22:45,014
A look! Something that says
that we're on the same side here!

1180
01:22:46,054 --> 01:22:48,534
Isn't this the moment
where one of us says:

1181
01:22:48,854 --> 01:22:50,854
"This is ridiculous.
We love each other.

1182
01:22:51,094 --> 01:22:54,214
All couples go through this.
Let's give it another try"?

1183
01:23:07,334 --> 01:23:09,334
It was supposed to rain today.

1184
01:23:10,773 --> 01:23:12,213
Glad it didn't.

1185
01:23:13,413 --> 01:23:14,693
Me too.

1186
01:23:19,253 --> 01:23:21,413
Turn here. If you take Sepulveda....

1187
01:23:24,053 --> 01:23:25,013
What?

1188
01:23:26,453 --> 01:23:27,573
Nothing.

1189
01:23:41,172 --> 01:23:43,572
Do you, Katie, take Ben...

1190
01:23:43,812 --> 01:23:45,732
...to have and to hold...

1191
01:23:45,972 --> 01:23:48,132
...in sickness and in health...

1192
01:23:48,372 --> 01:23:50,292
...for better or for worse...

1193
01:23:50,692 --> 01:23:53,492
-...till death do you part?
-I do.

1194
01:23:56,932 --> 01:23:58,772
It's a boy.
It's a girl.

1195
01:23:58,932 --> 01:23:59,892
It's a bunny!

1196
01:24:00,132 --> 01:24:01,412
It's a home run!

1197
01:24:01,652 --> 01:24:02,932
It's chickenpox.

1198
01:24:03,092 --> 01:24:04,052
It's over.

1199
01:24:04,212 --> 01:24:05,492
I love you.

1200
01:24:05,732 --> 01:24:06,612
Damn you!

1201
01:24:06,772 --> 01:24:07,652
I love you.

1202
01:24:08,612 --> 01:24:09,492
Damn it!

1203
01:24:09,651 --> 01:24:10,691
I love you.

1204
01:24:10,931 --> 01:24:12,611
I love you. I love you. I love you.

1205
01:24:12,771 --> 01:24:14,131
I hate you!

1206
01:24:14,371 --> 01:24:16,211
Fuck me. Fuck me.

1207
01:24:16,451 --> 01:24:17,331
Fuck you!

1208
01:24:20,851 --> 01:24:21,971
I love you.

1209
01:24:22,211 --> 01:24:23,171
I'm pregnant.

1210
01:24:23,411 --> 01:24:24,611
My goldfish died.

1211
01:24:24,771 --> 01:24:25,891
My hamster died.

1212
01:24:26,051 --> 01:24:26,931
My father's dying.

1213
01:24:27,171 --> 01:24:28,371
I'm pregnant.

1214
01:24:48,610 --> 01:24:50,530
Maybe we should separate.

1215
01:25:30,129 --> 01:25:32,129
Mom! Dad!

1216
01:25:32,369 --> 01:25:33,649
You ready?

1217
01:25:38,369 --> 01:25:40,768
What's up? It's good to see you.

1218
01:25:41,008 --> 01:25:42,448
How you doing?

1219
01:25:43,728 --> 01:25:44,848
What's the matter?

1220
01:25:45,328 --> 01:25:47,648
She just missed you, that's all.

1221
01:25:47,808 --> 01:25:50,288
You've both just grown so big.

1222
01:25:50,528 --> 01:25:53,088
Look at you guys.
I hardly recognize you. Wait.

1223
01:25:54,208 --> 01:25:55,328
Which one is Erin?

1224
01:25:56,208 --> 01:25:57,728
Check it out, Dad.

1225
01:25:58,368 --> 01:26:02,208
I guess we know what your high
is today. "Best All-Around Camper."

1226
01:26:02,368 --> 01:26:03,808
Congratulations. Look.

1227
01:26:04,048 --> 01:26:07,328
I guess this calls for a celebration!
Come on! Riverdance!

1228
01:26:07,968 --> 01:26:10,447
I'm the best all-around Riverdancer

1229
01:26:10,687 --> 01:26:14,047
Come on. Kind of like
a little "Latin Lupe Lu" thing.

1230
01:26:14,847 --> 01:26:16,367
Go with the big finish!

1231
01:26:16,847 --> 01:26:18,367
Come on! What?

1232
01:26:18,687 --> 01:26:22,047
-I have to see these kids next summer.
-Come on, we're hungry.

1233
01:26:22,767 --> 01:26:24,847
Okay. All right.

1234
01:26:30,527 --> 01:26:31,487
Let's go home.

1235
01:26:44,446 --> 01:26:46,766
I think we should go to Chow Fun's.

1236
01:26:55,246 --> 01:26:56,766
Chow Fun's?

1237
01:26:59,006 --> 01:27:01,646
We agreed that we
couldn't talk at Chow Fun's.

1238
01:27:02,206 --> 01:27:03,486
I know.

1239
01:27:05,326 --> 01:27:06,446
What are you saying?

1240
01:27:06,766 --> 01:27:08,765
I'm saying Chow Fun's.

1241
01:27:13,085 --> 01:27:16,125
Are you saying Chow Fun's
because you can't face telling them?

1242
01:27:16,365 --> 01:27:18,925
If that's why, don't say Chow Fun's.

1243
01:27:19,165 --> 01:27:23,485
That's not why. I'm saying Chow Fun's
because we're an "us."

1244
01:27:24,765 --> 01:27:26,925
There's a history here...

1245
01:27:27,165 --> 01:27:29,965
...and histories
don't happen overnight.

1246
01:27:30,765 --> 01:27:32,685
In Mesopotamia or ancient Troy...

1247
01:27:32,925 --> 01:27:36,845
...or somewhere, there are cities
built on top of other cities...

1248
01:27:37,005 --> 01:27:40,284
...but I don't wanna build
another city. I like this city.

1249
01:27:40,524 --> 01:27:42,204
I know where we keep the Bactine...

1250
01:27:42,444 --> 01:27:45,804
...and what mood you're in
by which eyebrow is higher.

1251
01:27:46,044 --> 01:27:50,684
You always know that I'm quiet in
the morning and compensate accordingly.

1252
01:27:51,004 --> 01:27:53,644
That's a dance you perfect over time.

1253
01:27:53,884 --> 01:27:56,764
And it's much harder
than I thought it would be...

1254
01:27:57,004 --> 01:28:01,324
...but there's more good than bad.
And you don't just give up!

1255
01:28:01,564 --> 01:28:04,044
And it's not for the sake
of the children.

1256
01:28:04,284 --> 01:28:06,364
But they're great kids, aren't they?

1257
01:28:06,684 --> 01:28:09,163
And we made them!
I mean, think about that.

1258
01:28:09,483 --> 01:28:12,523
There were no people there,
and then there were people.

1259
01:28:12,763 --> 01:28:14,203
And then they grew.

1260
01:28:14,843 --> 01:28:18,683
I won't be able to say to some
stranger, "Josh has your hands" ...

1261
01:28:18,923 --> 01:28:22,523
...or "Remember how Erin threw up
at the Lincoln Memorial?"

1262
01:28:22,763 --> 01:28:25,643
And I'll try to relax.

1263
01:28:26,763 --> 01:28:30,523
Let's face it, anybody will have
traits that get on your nerves.

1264
01:28:30,843 --> 01:28:34,763
Why shouldn't it be your annoying
traits? I'm no day at the beach.

1265
01:28:35,003 --> 01:28:38,682
But I do have a good sense
of direction, so I can find the beach.

1266
01:28:38,842 --> 01:28:41,242
Which is not a criticism of yours...

1267
01:28:42,522 --> 01:28:44,442
...it's just a strength of mine.

1268
01:28:44,682 --> 01:28:49,642
God, you're a good friend.
And good friends are hard to find.

1269
01:28:50,842 --> 01:28:53,082
Charlotte said that
in Charlotte's Web.

1270
01:28:53,322 --> 01:28:55,562
I love the way you read that to Erin.

1271
01:28:55,802 --> 01:28:58,682
You take on the voice of Wilbur
with such commitment...

1272
01:28:58,922 --> 01:29:00,602
...even when you're bone tired.

1273
01:29:00,842 --> 01:29:04,922
That speaks volumes about character.
And ultimately...

1274
01:29:05,482 --> 01:29:08,681
...isn't that what it comes down to?
What a person's made of?

1275
01:29:09,161 --> 01:29:12,521
Because that girl
in the pith helmet...

1276
01:29:12,761 --> 01:29:14,441
...is still in here.

1277
01:29:17,721 --> 01:29:20,921
I didn't even know she existed
until I met you.

1278
01:29:21,081 --> 01:29:23,241
And I'm afraid if you leave...

1279
01:29:24,201 --> 01:29:26,041
...I may never see her again.

1280
01:29:26,281 --> 01:29:30,041
Even though I said you beat her
out of me. Isn't that the paradox?

1281
01:29:30,281 --> 01:29:33,721
Haven't we hit the essential paradox?
Give and take, push and pull.

1282
01:29:33,961 --> 01:29:36,920
The best of times, the worst of times.
Dickens said it best.

1283
01:29:37,160 --> 01:29:41,000
The Jack Sprat of it. He could eat
no fat. His wife could eat no lean.

1284
01:29:41,240 --> 01:29:45,480
But that doesn't apply here, does it?
I guess what I'm trying to say is...

1285
01:29:46,920 --> 01:29:49,400
...I'm saying Chow Fun's because...

1286
01:29:50,040 --> 01:29:51,640
...I love you.

1287
01:30:00,920 --> 01:30:02,280
I love you too.

1288
01:30:10,279 --> 01:30:11,879
Did you hear that, kids?

1289
01:30:12,199 --> 01:30:14,759
Your mom wants to go to Chow Fun's!

1290
01:30:15,799 --> 01:30:18,519
Isn't that great?
I love Chow Fun's!

1291
01:30:18,839 --> 01:30:21,319
The egg rolls are good,
but not that good.

1292
01:30:21,639 --> 01:30:23,559
The egg rolls are fantastic!

1293
01:30:23,719 --> 01:30:25,959
They're warm, crispy,
greasy as all hell.

1294
01:30:26,279 --> 01:30:28,919
-Everything you want in an egg roll!
-Exactly!

1295
01:30:29,159 --> 01:30:30,599
High/Low. Erin, you first.

1296
01:30:30,919 --> 01:30:33,799
My high for the summer is,
Austin wrote me 111 times.

1297
01:30:34,119 --> 01:30:36,438
How did you come up
with High/Low anyway?

1298
01:30:36,678 --> 01:30:39,318
I don't know.
But I've got another game.

1299
01:30:39,478 --> 01:30:42,278
I'm thinking of seven words.
What are they?

1300
01:30:42,678 --> 01:30:44,358
Do I get a hint?

1301
01:30:44,678 --> 01:30:45,478
A category?

1302
01:30:45,718 --> 01:30:48,758
-Any seven words in English.
-That's right.

1303
01:30:49,078 --> 01:30:50,278
Fair enough.

1304
01:30:51,318 --> 01:30:54,038
"MacArthur Park is melting
in the dark."

1305
01:30:57,398 --> 01:31:00,518
"And they lived happily ever after."

1306
01:31:01,398 --> 01:31:03,958
That's six words,
but you're very close.

1307
01:31:05,238 --> 01:31:08,517
"And they lived mostly happily
ever after"?

1308
01:31:09,317 --> 01:31:10,677
I hope so.

1309
01:31:11,397 --> 01:31:12,997
I think so.

1310
01:31:14,917 --> 01:31:16,117
Think so?

1311
01:31:16,677 --> 01:31:17,877
I do.

1312
01:31:19,237 --> 01:31:20,517
I do...

1313
01:31:20,997 --> 01:31:22,117
...too.

1314
01:35:17,697 --> 01:35:27,001
Synchronization by ShooCat

